1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
[Stran]
 
[Song]

2
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Dem baş temaşevanên me yê hêja, temaşevanên me yê ezîz.
 
Good day, our precious viewers, our dear viewers.

3
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Ji qenala we, qenala Hatim Li Efrîn em carek din we silav
dikin.
 
From your channel, Hatim Li Efrîn channel, we greet you once
again.

4
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Îro jî bi taybetî em ê berê xwe bidin gundê Gazê.
 
Today, specifically, we will head towards the village of
Gazê.

5
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Em ê li nav dar û berên gundê Gazê bin, em ê derbasî gundê
Gazê bibin.
 
We will be among the trees and nature of Gazê village, we
will enter the village of Gazê.

6
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Em ê navê gund û gundiyan nas bikin, em ê silavên xwe bi
gundîyan re bidin.
 
We will get to know the name of the village and the
villagers, we will give our greetings to the villagers.

7
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Em ê dîroka vî gundî bi hev re nas bikin.
 
We will learn the history of this village together.

8
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Em ê binêrin navê Gazê ji ku tê.
 
We will see where the name Gazê comes from.

9
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Ev gund çend sal in hatiye avakirin? Kesên destpêkê ku
hatine malbata xwe li vî gundî ava kirine kîjan malbat in?
 
How many years has this village been built? Who are the
first people that came and built their family in this
village, which families are they?

10
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Di vê xelekê de bi pirtişkî em ê bi hev re nas bikin.
 
In this episode, we will briefly get to know this together.

11
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Berî em derbasî gund bibin, silav û rêz ji gundiyan û ji
kurdan re li tevahiya cîhanê.
 
Before we enter the village, greetings and respect to the
villagers and to the Kurds all over the world.

12
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Silava min ji kekê Kerîwan re li bajarê Amerîka dimîne û
hevalê min e, ji gundê Gazê ye.
 
My greetings to brother Kerîwan who lives in the city of
America, he is my friend and is from the village of Gazê.

13
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Niha li Amerîka dimîne, silav û hurmet ji wî û malbata wî re
bi tevahî.
 
He now lives in America, greetings and respects to him and
his entire family.

14
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Silav û rêz ji şêniyên gundê Gazê re.
 
Greetings and respect to the residents of Gazê village.

15
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Lê niha jî bi me re bin ez û Hîn, em derbasî nava dar û
berên gundê Gazê bibin.
 
But now be with us, Hîn and I, let's enter the trees and
nature of Gazê village.

16
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Em ê gundê Gazê bi hev re nas bikin.
 
We will get to know Gazê village together.

17
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Berî em dest bi vîdeoya xwe bikin em sipasiya şêrwanên xwe
dikin ji ber ku wî taswîra dironê ji me re girtiye.
 
Before we start our video, we thank our warriors because he
took the drone footage for us.

18
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Lê niha jî bi me re bin ez û Hîn bi dilkî xweş û geş em ê
derbasî gundê Gazê bibin.
 
But now be with us, Hîn and I, with a happy and bright
heart, we will enter the village of Gazê.

19
00:02:42,000 --> 00:03:02,000
[Muzîk / Dîmenê Dironê]
 
[Music / Drone Footage]

20
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Belê temaşevanên me yê hêja em niha kekê Neşet em gihîştin
ser bîrekê.
 
Yes, our precious viewers, we and brother Neşet have now
reached a well.

21
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Em niha li ser bîrekê ne, ev bîra Hecî Mûrad e.
 
We are now at a well, this is Hecî Mûrad's well.

22
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Ev bîra jî, çîrokên xwe hene bixwe. Gelek çîrokên wê hene.
 
This well also has its own stories. It has many stories.

23
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Em ê niha van çîrokan bi kekê Neşet re parve bikin û pirsên
xwe bikin ser vê bîrê ji kekê Neşet re bikin.
 
We will now share these stories with brother Neşet and ask
him our questions about this well.

24
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Bîr e, lê ev bîr di nav dar û beran de ye.
 
It is a well, but this well is among trees and nature.

25
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Kekê Neşet, di destpêkê de li ser vê bîrê ji me re xeber de.
 
Brother Neşet, firstly tell us something about this well.

26
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Bixêr hatî heval. Em dibêjin, ji mêj da çi dibêjin...
 
Welcome, friend. We say, what have they been saying for a
long time...

27
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Ku dema ku bîrek tê çêkirin, av jê dixiqîne.
 
That when a well is made, water flows from it.

28
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Bîr ava wê xelas nabe, lê bi heriyê tê dagirtin. Her sal yan
du salan yan sê salan, gundî tên amade dibin û vedikin.
 
The water of the well doesn't finish, but it gets filled
with mud. Every year or two or three years, the villagers
come, get ready, and open it.

29
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Yanî gundî tên vedikin, heriyê wê derdixin. Em tenê weha
vedikin her qonaxekê, dema dixitime.
 
Meaning the villagers come and open it, taking out its mud.
We just open it like this every stage, when it gets clogged.

30
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Dema ku tu paqij nekî, ew tijî dibe û xirab dibe.
 
When you don't clean it, it fills up and gets ruined.

31
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Yek ji van bîran jî ev e. Ev bîra Şêxmîr e... Erê navê wê
heman navê Şêxmîr e.
 
One of these wells is this one. This is Şêxmîr's well...
Yes, its name is the same as Şêxmîr.

32
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Navê wê jî nêzîkî wê ye bixwe. Em wek mînak nêzîkî hezar kes
in em li vir rûdinin. Em hatin me ev bîr pak kir...
 
Its name is close to it too. For example, we are about a
thousand people living here. We came and cleaned this
well...

33
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Ev av jî ji ku derdikeve kekê Neşet? Welleh ava we pir şêrîn
e ha maaşallah!
 
Where does this water come from, brother Neşet? By God, your
water is very sweet, mashallah!

34
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Ev av, ev çaviyê wê di nav erdê de ye. Çaviyek jê dertê...
 
This water, its spring is inside the earth. A spring comes
out of it...

35
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Çaviyek heye ji wê bîrê, ew bîra ser riya Dargirê heye ya
jêr.
 
There is a spring from that well, the well on the road to
Dargirê, the lower one.

36
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Jêra wê bîrê dikişe vir, û ji vir jî dikişe diçe geliyê,
diçe darî geliyê. Ser riya Dargirê.
 
Below that well it flows here, and from here it flows to the
valley, towards the valley. On the road to Dargirê.

37
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Ava gundê we jî pir paqij e, pir xweş e.
 
The water of your village is very clean, very nice.

38
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Zebeşekî teyke, dê yekî biterqîne!
 
Throw a watermelon in it, it will crack one open!

39
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Maaşallah bîzê... maaşallah.
 
Mashallah to the ice... mashallah.

40
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Ev gundê we jî pir hênik e kekê Neşet. Ev der pir hênik e a
rastî.
 
This village of yours is also very cool, brother Neşet. This
place is very cool to be honest.

41
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Ev bixwe... ava bîrê ye. Dibe ku ev bîr sêsed sal be, çarsed
sal be, pêncsed sal be, kes nizane. Pir kevnar e ev bîr.
 
This itself... is well water. This well might be three
hundred years old, four hundred years old, five hundred
years old, nobody knows. This well is very ancient.

42
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Ev cihek e, yanî wek mînak em tên serî...
 
This is a place, I mean for example we come to it...

43
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:19,000
Em tên nanê xwe dixwin. Malbat tên ji Efrînê, mîna seyranê.
 
We come and eat our food. Families come from Efrîn, like a
picnic.

44
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Yanî wek seyrangehek e. Tên vir rûkê xwe xweş dikin û wextê
xwe derbas dikin miletê me.
 
I mean it's like a picnic spot. Our people come here, make
themselves comfortable and spend their time.

45
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Belê wele. Niha em piçekî dûrî darê herin û li dora wê
bigerin kekê Neşet.
 
Yes indeed. Now let's go a bit away from the tree and walk
around it, brother Neşet.

46
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Ev bixwe bîrek e... Ev dar, çend caran hişk bûn, lê carek
din hêşîn bûn û mezin bûn.
 
This is a well itself... This tree, it dried up a few times,
but it sprouted again and grew big.

47
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Bîrekî pir kevn e.
 
It is a very old well.

48
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Bîrekî pir kevn e. Çûk û heywan tên avê vedixwin.
 
It is a very old well. Birds and animals come and drink
water.

49
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Li serê wê wek teştan tê dîtin, çûk avê jê vedixwin û heywan
avê jê vedixwin.
 
On top of it, it looks like bowls, birds drink water from it
and animals drink water from it.

50
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
Bîr bixwe ne kûr e. Dibe 4 metre be.
 
The well itself is not deep. It might be 4 meters.

51
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Ev der çaviyê wê ye... lingê xwe yê ku tu dikî navê, wek
pêpelûk e.
 
This is its spring... where you put your foot in, it's like
a stair.

52
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:03,000
Em pak dikin, ji qirêjiyan, ji qirş û qalan pak dikin dema
ku gemarî dibe.
 
We clean it, we clean it from dirt, from twigs and debris
when it gets dirty.

53
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Bixwe ev av di biharê de... digihîje du metreyan, an jî
metreyek.
 
Actually this water in spring... reaches two meters, or one
meter.

54
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,000
Sal ku xweş be xweş be, nêzîkî devê bîrê dibe.
 
When the year is good and fertile, it gets close to the
mouth of the well.

55
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Û sal ku ne xweş be... ev 4 sal Xwedê neda baran nebarî...
Ev ava me li herêmê, yanî metreyek e.
 
And when the year is not good... these 4 years God didn't
give and it didn't rain... This water of ours in the region,
is like one meter.

56
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Metreyek e, metreyek û nîv e. Yanî ava wê berdewam e, qet
qut nabe.
 
It's one meter, a meter and a half. Meaning its water is
continuous, it never cuts off.

57
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:41,000
[Dengê Avê]
 
[Sound of Water]

58
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Em di vê rê de herin kekê Neşet. Ev zinar e ev dar in...
 
Let's go this way brother Neşet. These are rocks, these are
trees...

59
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Ev zinar e.
 
This is a rock.

60
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Ev zinar in... ev dar in...
 
These are rocks... these are trees...

61
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Ev zinar... ew jî...
 
This is a rock... and that...

62
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Ev dîwar, xwediyê gund e?
 
This wall, does it belong to the village?

63
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Ev bîra Xwedê ye. Ev dîwar jî dîwarê bîrê ye. Gundiyan dika
wê çêkirine.
 
This is God's well. This wall is also the wall of the well.
The villagers have made a platform for it.

64
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,000
Ku gundî li ser rûnin?
 
So the villagers can sit on it?

65
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Erê, gundî li vir rûdinin. Bîr ev e.
 
Yes, the villagers sit here. This is the well.

66
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Ev hemî darên gûzan in bixwe.
 
These are all walnut trees actually.

67
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:17,000
Gûz in, gûz in, sêv in, erê...
 
Walnuts, they are walnuts, apples, yes...

68
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Hemiya wan gûz in sêv in.
 
All of them are walnuts and apples.

69
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,000
Erê. Hemî cûre hene.
 
Yes. There are all kinds.

70
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:37,000
[Muzîk / Dengê Xwezayê]
 
[Music / Sound of Nature]

71
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Li gor vê em dizanin, li gund de gelek dar in.
 
According to this we know, there are many trees in the
village.

72
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
Eşya te anîn?
 
Did you bring your things?

73
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:48,000
Eşya wekî min nedizanî, tişt hene min nedizanî...
 
Things like I didn't know, there are things I didn't know...

74
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Welah em jî herêma nizanin em... min nizanî em di herêmê de
diçin...
 
By God we don't know the region either... I didn't know we
are going into the region...

75
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:56,000
Min qet gund de wek van dîmênan nedîbû, min nediçû herêmê
da...
 
I had never seen such scenes in the village, I wasn't going
into the region...

76
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Min digot ka ez bêm herêmê ez binerim...
 
I was saying let me come to the region and take a look...

77
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:04,000
Weleh ez di hatim, ev di ber min re derbas dibe û min nedît.
 
By God I used to come, this passes right by me and I didn't
see it.

78
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Û hûn niha gihîştin wê herêmê, ev herêm çi ye?
 
And now you reached that region, what is this region?

79
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:11,000
A ev a. Bi xwedê min di gund de wek van dera...
 
Oh this. By God, places like this in the village for me...

80
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Ev av jî di vir de heye...
 
There is also this water here...

81
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:17,000
A ev? Ev av a... ev bixwe gundê we... darên herêmê, a ev e.
 
Oh this? This water... this itself is your village... the
trees of the region, oh this is it.

82
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:22,000
A ev cî, dema çûk û heywanan, xenzîrên navçeyê de dihatin.
 
Oh this place, when birds and animals, boars of the district
used to come.

83
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Çi heywanatên deştê hebûn, dihatin jê av vedixwarin.
 
Whatever animals of the plains there were, they used to come
and drink water from it.

84
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:31,000
Miletê me jî dema ku mînak dema pezên xwe didoştin, dihatin
di ber vê avê de rûdiniştin.
 
Our people also when for example they milked their sheep,
they would come and sit by this water.

85
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:34,000
Li gundê we jî mirov pez diçêrînin ser gund de...
 
In your village too, people graze sheep above the village...

86
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Bes bihara gund... bihara te yê wekî min dîtî sal baş be,
maaşallah dîtin xelkê her tişt e.
 
But the spring of the village... your spring like I saw if
the year is good, mashallah the people's view is everything.

87
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:44,000
Cota wan çawa ye? Min nedîtî, ka zêde nakin cot?
 
How is their plowing? I didn't see, don't they plow a lot?

88
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:48,000
Belê zêde ye... lê ne wek salan e...
 
Yes it's a lot... but not like the years...

89
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:58,000
[Muzîk]
 
[Music]

90
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:02,000
Ev çi ye kekê Neşet?
 
What is this, brother Neşet?

91
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:09,000
Ev gela ye... ev gela, a ev. A ev tirş e, pispis tê gotin,
pispiska çiyê...
 
This is leaves... this is leaves, oh this. Oh this is sour,
it's called pispis, mountain pispis...

92
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Sivik e, tehl e? Sift e. Pispis.
 
Is it light, is it bitter? It's sift. Pispis.

93
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:15,000
Pispisoka tirş e... Ev tirş e.
 
It is sour pispisok... This is sour.

94
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:21,000
A... Subhanallah... çi tiştên ecêb li herêmê hene.
 
Ah... Subhanallah... what strange things exist in the
region.

95
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:25,000
Tiştên cîhanî ye...
 
It's world class things...

96
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:45,000
[Stran] Efrîna min... Efrîna min, şêrîn... Efrîna min,
şêrîn... Xeyala min... jiyana min... Efrîna min... Efrîna
min...
 
[Song] My Efrîn... my sweet Efrîn... my sweet Efrîn... My
dream... my life... my Efrîn... my Efrîn...

97
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Em hatin kekê Xelîl, em qenala Hatim Li Efrîn in...
 
We came brother Xelîl, we are the Hatim Li Efrîn channel...

98
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Wele hûn gelek bi xêr hatin ser çavan!
 
By God you are very welcome, upon my eyes!

99
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,000
Em hatin, em qenala Hatim Li Efrîn in...
 
We came, we are the Hatim Li Efrîn channel...

100
00:09:53,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Ser çavan hûn hatin...
 
You came upon my eyes...

101
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:47,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja niha jî em derbasî gundê Gazê
bûn.
 
Yes, our dear viewers, now we have crossed into the village
of Gazê.

102
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:51,000
Bi me ra bin, em ê derbasî malbatekê bin, malbateke xwedî
nêrî.
 
Stay with us, we will visit a household, a household with
perspective.

103
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,000
Em ê li wê malbetê rûnin. Em ê nîvroya xwe di wê malbetê de
bin.
 
We will sit in that household. We will spend our afternoon
in that household.

104
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Em ê hinekî li ser dîroka vî gundî zanibin.
 
We will learn a bit about the history of this village.

105
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:18,000
Em ê bi hev ra vî gundî nas bikin.
 
Together we will get to know this village.

106
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,000
Em te nas bikin xalo.
 
Let us get to know you, uncle.

107
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:47,000
Navê min Hesen e, leqebê min Hemedî dibêjin.
 
My name is Hesen, they call me by my nickname Hemedî.

108
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,000
Bavê...
 
Father of...

109
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,000
Bavê Hesen.
 
Father of Hesen.

110
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Bavê Hesen.
 
Father of Hesen.

111
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:55,000
Bavê Hesen, em berî her tiştî spasiya we dikin, ber ku îro
em nîvroya xwe li gundê Gazê ne.
 
Father of Hesen, first of all we thank you, because today we
are spending our afternoon in the village of Gazê.

112
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,000
Ser çava, ehlen we sehlen.
 
Upon my eyes, you are very welcome.

113
00:11:56,000 --> 00:12:01,000
Ez dixwazim, ez û te em çîrokeke xwe rûnin em li ser gundê
Gazê xeber bidin.
 
I want you and I to sit down and talk about the story of the
village of Gazê.

114
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,000
Ya ehlen we sehlen, baş e, bi ser çava.
 
You are very welcome, alright, upon my eyes.

115
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,000
Dîroka gund em zanibin.
 
Let's learn the history of the village.

116
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,000
Ehlen, ser çava, erê.
 
Welcome, upon my eyes, yes.

117
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Zehmet meke yabo.
 
Don't trouble yourself, uncle.

118
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:14,000
Gundê me... Gundê me... Mala Hesen Efendî hene.
 
Our village... Our village... The family of Hesen Efendî is
here.

119
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:19,000
Û bi wî aliyê din de jî dîsa malên Birîmê Hecî... Berê em
dibêjin mala Birîmê Hecî hene.
 
And on the other side, there is also the family of Birîmê
Hecî... We used to say the family of Birîmê Hecî is here.

120
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:23,000
Ew jî aîleyeke pênc şeş pismam in.
 
They are also a family of five or six cousins.

121
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:26,000
Û gundê me jî, mala Hesen Efendî, aîleyeke mezin e.
 
And our village too, the family of Hesen Efendî, is a big
family.

122
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Yanî Mala Ehmedê Îbiş e, Mala Îbo e...
 
I mean, the family of Ehmedê Îbiş, the family of Îbo...

123
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:35,000
Û... li vî milî jî dîsa Mala Ebolî heye, ew jî ji Hesen
Efendiyan in.
 
And... on this side again there is the family of Ebolî, they
are also from the Hesen Efendîs.

124
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:38,000
Mala Evdî Gênco, ew jî ji Hesen Efendiyan in.
 
The family of Evdî Gênco, they are also from the Hesen
Efendîs.

125
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Em bêjin Evdî Gênco, ew jî ji Hesen Efendiyan e... el
muhîm...
 
We say Evdî Gênco, he is also from the Hesen Efendîs...
anyway...

126
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:49,000
Û Mala Eqêş jî, ew jî... cîranên me gundê me ne, ew jî sê
çar mal, paşê hatin cem me el muhîm...
 
And the family of Eqêş too, they are also... our neighbors
in our village, they are three or four households, later
they came to us, anyway...

127
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:54,000
Hesen Efendî berê erdê xwe li Til Hemîs bû.
 
Hesen Efendî's land used to be in Til Hemîs.

128
00:12:54,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Li vir Hesen Efendî di derheqê hukmê xwe, li Til Hemîs hukim
dikir.
 
Here, regarding his rule, Hesen Efendî ruled in Til Hemîs.

129
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:05,000
Paşê jî... wa dibêjin ew wehdê dera da... fîlim çêbûn...
 
Then later... they say that during that time... things
happened...

130
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Kes nema, bi dest evê ket... Mala Heyder Axa ket.
 
No one was left, it fell into the hands... the hands of the
Heyder Axa family.

131
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:14,000
Mala Heyder Axa jî... Wextê ku em lê gerîn...
 
The Heyder Axa family too... When we came back to it...

132
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

133
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Wextê ku em lê gerîn em bicî nekirin.
 
When we came back, they didn't settle us.

134
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,000
Got em milkan nadin we ya.
 
They said we won't give you the properties.

135
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Bes weyê dibêjin ew jî ji Mala Heyder Axa, paşê, el muhîm...
 
But they say that from the Heyder Axa family, later on,
anyway...

136
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Mêrikek zevt kirin, û derê jî islaha bela kirin.
 
They caught a man, and then they distributed the reform.

137
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,000
Kesî me tune bû meselê, bikişîne û bikşîne.
 
We had no one, for example, to pull strings.

138
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,000
Gelê xwedî neqîb ekî bela kirin.
 
They distributed it to the people who had a captain.

139
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Paşê jî xwendewanên me derketin.
 
Later on, our students emerged.

140
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Heta ku xwendewanên me derketin tedî wezîet dîna ha çû, ha
çû...
 
Until our students emerged, you saw the situation of the
world went on like this...

141
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Ha çû, ha çû ta noka em gihan van deran.
 
It went on and on until now, we reached this point.

142
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Xeyrî derê...
 
Other than that...

143
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Ji niha pê ve wekî meîşetê me... meîşetê me çawa ye?
 
From now on, like our livelihood... how is our livelihood?

144
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Çawiyê jî na... meîşetê me ne zêde ye.
 
It is not a lot... our livelihood is not much.

145
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Welah em gund belengazî pê ava bûne.
 
By God, our village was built on poverty.

146
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:55,000
Û xwendewanên me Elhemdulîlah... cem me xwendavan pir in.
 
And our students, thank God... we have a lot of students.

147
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:59,000
Duktor jî hene, muhendis jî hene, usta jî hene...
 
We have doctors, we have engineers, we have masters...

148
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,000
Yanî bi vî şeklî ewan in.
 
I mean, they are like that.

149
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Xwediyê bekalorya û tişt hene.
 
There are those with baccalaureates and such.

150
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,000
Yanî gî hene Elhemdulillah bi bereket, bes meselen...
 
I mean, they are all there, thank God, with blessing, but
for example...

151
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Çi gundek wek we gotî, çêke, ava bike...
 
Like a village you talked about, build it, establish it...

152
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,000
Bes evê xwe rind e. Xwendavanan...
 
But this itself is good. The students...

153
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Musteqbela xortên xwe yê, gî xwendavan in.
 
The future of their youth, they are all students.

154
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

155
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Bi kêmanî... ji sedî bîst ne xwendavan in.
 
At least... twenty percent are not students.

156
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,000
Ê din gî xwendavan in Elhemdulillah.
 
The rest are all students, thank God.

157
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:21,000
Ê xwendavanên me di neqra de e pir çûne li dervane. Li
derve.
 
Now, our students, many have gone abroad. Abroad.

158
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,000
Berê hewşê giya hebûn. Hevşê giya hene.
 
Before, there were grass courtyards. They are there.

159
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Heleb jî hebûn... Efrîn jî hebûn.
 
They were in Aleppo too... They were in Afrin too.

160
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Ê niha qey tişkî me perîşan bûn. Fîlmik...
 
Now, perhaps things have become miserable for us. A film...

161
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,000
Çûn derve, der bûn, niha deştê de mal hene, xwendavan tê
hene...
 
They went abroad, they got out, now there are houses in the
plains, there are students in them...

162
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Muhendis tê hene, mehendist hene.
 
There are engineers in them, there are engineers.

163
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:39,000
Man li henê... tên hene. Tiştek tune li derekî.
 
They stayed here... they are coming. There is nothing
anywhere.

164
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Û da meîşetên me jî ew e... miletê me çi ewkî tiştek wê de,
ew e.
 
And our livelihood is that... our people, whatever it is
over there, that is it.

165
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Bavê Hesen, te ser vî gundî xeber da.
 
Father of Hesen, you talked about this village.

166
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Ez dixwazim em zanibin, ev gundê kevin e, çend sal e hatiye
avakirin?
 
I want us to know, this ancient village, how many years ago
was it built?

167
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:58,000
Gundê me, gundekî kevn e, kevnar e.
 
Our village is an old village, it is ancient.

168
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Gundekî kevnar e, bê sînor sal e.
 
It is an ancient village, with limitless years.

169
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,000
Ji gundên nahala weşan e, derketine.
 
It is from the villages of the broadcast valleys, they
emerged.

170
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Me berê da got tebeqa ye.
 
We previously said it is a level.

171
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

172
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,000
Ê tebeqa evê xwe, gundê xirab bûne.
 
This level itself, they were ruined villages.

173
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Vî gundî teqrîben ji heftsed salî heye.
 
This village has existed for approximately seven hundred
years.

174
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,000
Heftsed sal e hatiye ava kirin, ev gund?
 
Has this village been built for seven hundred years?

175
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

176
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Ê navê Gazê, ji ku hat, ez dixwazim vî jî zanibim?
 
And where did the name Gazê come from, I want to know this
too?

177
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:19,000
Ê navê Gazê ne... cîh xwe bilind e, pê ra dibêjin gundê
Gazê.
 
The name Gazê... its location is high, so they call it the
village of Gazê.

178
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

179
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Wî cihê xwe yê bilind e...
 
Its high place...

180
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:24,000
Em dikarin bibêjin kîjan gund e, gundê mezin e?
 
Can we say which village it is, is it a big village?

181
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Na.
 
No.

182
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:28,000
A ji... Qulbê... Keferdelê jor e ne.
 
From... Qulbê... Upper Keferdelê.

183
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

184
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:32,000
Û aliyê şerqî Maritê heye.
 
And on the eastern side, Maritê is there.

185
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Û şîmalî gundî mezin heye.
 
And in the north, there is the big village.

186
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,000
Û aliyê xerbî jî... Ka Xirê... em di wî sêyiyê bûn teqrîben,
xerb e...
 
And on the western side... Ka Xirê... we were in that third
approximately, it is the west...

187
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Ew dikeve sêyê wî heye.
 
It falls into its third.

188
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

189
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:44,000
Ka Xirê... ew derne na ne... Şît e...
 
Ka Xirê... those places are not... it's Şît...

190
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,000
Dayê...
 
Mother...

191
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

192
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,000
Lê wekî ku te mezin kir... navê te çiye?
 
But as you raised... what is your name?

193
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Ebû Evdo ya Şare dibêjin. Dibe Ebû Evdo.
 
They say Ebû Evdo of Şare. Let it be Ebû Evdo.

194
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,000
Ser herdu çava.
 
Upon both my eyes.

195
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,000
Ehlen we sehlen.
 
You are very welcome.

196
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Ez dixwazim çîrokek te ji me ra xebere de, te çawa jiyana
xwe di vî gundî de kir?
 
I want you to tell us a story, how did you live your life in
this village?

197
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,000
Tu çend sal in, tu bûka vî gundî yî? Da tu bi xwe ji kîjan
gundî yî?
 
How many years have you been the bride of this village? And
which village are you from yourself?

198
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Gundê min.
 
My village.

199
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

200
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:08,000
Em ji vî gundî ne.
 
We are from this village.

201
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:14,000
Hema wekî... sî... sî sal zêde bûn em li... sî... pênc sal,
em li Helebê bûn.
 
Just like... thirty... more than thirty years we were in...
thirty... five years, we were in Aleppo.

202
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

203
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:21,000
Em hatin... me, bavê min, ez, şeş xwişkên min... û xwesiyê
min, qîzek pî re min e.
 
We came... us, my father, me, my six sisters... and my
mother-in-law, a girl is with me.

204
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

205
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:25,000
Em teva ha bidin bûn. Çar salan em teva ha bibûn.
 
We were all given like this. For four years we were all
together.

206
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Em dibûn ewê ciyê... şeş xwişkan em teva ha bidin bûn.
 
We were in that place... six sisters we were all given like
this.

207
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:36,000
Em teva ha bidin bûn... me bi hev ra eşa... rût e, na bi
rût, şerq, ji kesî wê nabîst.
 
We were all given like this... together we had pain...
naked, not naked, east, no one heard it.

208
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:42,000
Berê xwende hebû... Mêvan hebû... Pir û didîtin di xwediyê
vî gundî.
 
In the past there was reading... There were guests... They
saw a lot in the owner of this village.

209
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:48,000
E tê bi rût e... Xwedî û bexşan... Di eza kirim...
 
It comes naked... Owners and forgivers... I was tormented...

210
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:52,000
Wekî tu zanî mêvanên xwa ye biçîna... Keçkê xwa ye
dikirina...
 
As you know, the guests were going... The girls were
making...

211
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:56,000
Mêvanên xwa nanên xwe dixwarin, her yek bi derkî da diçû.
 
The guests ate their bread, each went out a door.

212
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

213
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,000
Ê me xwedan ne mabûn.
 
But we had no owners left.

214
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Ma tiştek nemabû?
 
Was nothing left?

215
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Ma nema.
 
Nothing was left.

216
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,000
Û mêranî jî berê re jî nema.
 
And bravery didn't remain like before either.

217
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Ew jî nema?
 
Did that not remain either?

218
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,000
Na.
 
No.

219
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,000
Û hezkirina yek sa ya hevdû jî ew da çar e?
 
And the love for one another, is it also a remedy?

220
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Sar e.
 
It is cold.

221
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,000
Berê baş xwedê.
 
In the past, it was good, by God.

222
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:16,000
Erê. Çi lawiyê xwe diçîn em prabîlê keçka diçûn Heleb...
Xwişkên min wî bûn.
 
Yes. Whatever sons went, we girls went to Aleppo... My
sisters were him.

223
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:22,000
Me mezin kirin, sîh û pênc sal e em li Heleb bûn... Û paşê
jî me dît zewicandin...
 
We raised them, for thirty-five years we were in Aleppo...
And then we saw they were married...

224
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,000
Me dît, elhemdulillah, me mal kirin.
 
We saw, thank God, we made a home.

225
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:29,000
Didil darvan ne, didil dar li Heleb in, û yêkî li bedere te
xwest e wê ji rehmê da... bû.
 
Two are in Darvan, two are in Dar in Aleppo, and one asked
outside, he passed away.

226
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Xwedê rehma xwe bike.
 
May God have mercy.

227
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:33,000
Û elhemdulillah di yê me de ne, hew nade yê me ne.
 
And thank God they are among us, they don't only give to us.

228
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:38,000
Na kesekî xirab di keve yê me, nav malika hew ne, me dê me
ne, di yê me ne kesek xirab tineye ew e.
 
No bad person falls among us, in the small house there
aren't, they are our mothers, among us there is no bad
person.

229
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:42,000
Em bi xelk re na, kesik xirab tineyare me...
 
We are not with the people, no bad person can stand us...

230
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Xelîqê Xwedê heye.
 
There is God's creation.

231
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

232
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Êdî... çib... dibe em seh li wî xwa pêşîn in yara.
 
Now... what... happens we look at the one before us now.

233
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:54,000
Elhemdulîllah hûn hatin ehlen we sehlen cemaeta we dî ehlen
we sehlen.
 
Thank God you came, you are very welcome, your group too is
very welcome.

234
00:17:54,000 --> 00:18:00,000
Bavê Hesen ez dixwazim... tiştekî te ser vî gundî hinekî ji
me ra xeber de...
 
Father of Hesen, I want... you to tell us a bit more about
this village...

235
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:05,000
Malbata tesîs hatiye gund, navê gund çî bû. Kîjan malbat ava
bû?
 
The family that was established in the village, what was the
name of the village? Which family was established?

236
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,000
Malbata tesîs di vir e ye, Mala Hesen... Hesen Efendî.
 
The established family here is, the family of Hesen... Hesen
Efendî.

237
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Mala Hesen Hesen Efendî.
 
The family of Hesen Hesen Efendî.

238
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

239
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Hatin vî gundî?
 
They came to this village?

240
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,000
Hatin gund ava kirin.
 
They came and built the village.

241
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,000
Piştî wan.
 
After them.

242
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,000
Gund ava kirin.
 
They built the village.

243
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,000
Gund ava kirin.
 
They built the village.

244
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,000
Erê, û milkê xwe jî li Til Hemîs bû.
 
Yes, and their property was also in Til Hemîs.

245
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Yanî haliyan her e Til Hemîs dibe.
 
I mean currently it still becomes Til Hemîs.

246
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:24,000
Rêka Gazê. Yê rêka Gazê ew Gazê ew e ne heye.
 
The Gazê road. The one of the Gazê road, that Gazê is there.

247
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

248
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,000
Mmmm.
 
Mmmm.

249
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:31,000
Û paşê dî, ew malbata pênc birên me ci di... pênc şeş
pismam.
 
And then later, that family of our five brothers... five or
six cousins.

250
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,000
Mala Birîmê Hecî.
 
The family of Birîmê Hecî.

251
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Da ew jî em berî wan hatine.. e em niha wijî em na giştin bi
hev re... elmuhîm.
 
And we came before them... and we now also haven't all
joined together... anyway.

252
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Bes wê dema ra xeber de...
 
Just talk about that time...

253
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:43,000
Erê... erê... em mekana dixebitîn û digotin mala evî paşê
gotin mala Birîmê Hecî em ne jî.
 
Yes... yes... we worked the place and they said the family
of this one, later they said the family of Birîmê Hecî, we
are not either.

254
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Ev mala me ne.
 
These are our families.

255
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:50,000
Û malan, a Hesen Efendî, a niha pênc şeş aîle... yanî.
 
And the families, of Hesen Efendî, now there are five or six
families... I mean.

256
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

257
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:55,000
E... ê, mala evê... Mala Mala Îbo. Pênc şeş bira ne.
 
Uh... uh, the family of this... The family of the Îbo
family. They are five or six brothers.

258
00:18:55,000 --> 00:19:00,000
Pismamê me ne û Mala Ehmedê Îbiş e û...
 
They are our cousins and the family of Ehmedê Îbiş and...

259
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:05,000
Mala Ebdî Gênco bi vî şiklî, wisa, di terfa mala Umer e jî
yê Mala Xelîc e jî ye ye.
 
The family of Ebdî Gênco in this way, like that, on the side
of Umer's family is also the family of Xelîc.

260
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Û... di dû ra, mala Êvî cîtiye ne. Mala qejiyan, na ew jî
cîranên gund in û...
 
And... later on, the family of Êvî is separated. The family
of the crows, no they are also neighbors of the village
and...

261
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:17,000
Û, mala vî de Mele Mihemed Evdê hav jî du aîle ne ew jî
esasê vî gundî, cemê me li gund in.
 
And, the family of this Mele Mihemed Evdê, they are also two
families, they are also the basis of this village, with us
in the village.

262
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

263
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:23,000
Yanî mi nake ev jî bi me re şirîkên gund in, rûniştvanên xwe
su baw û kalên xwe we aslen ne.
 
I mean, I don't consider these to be partners with us in the
village, residents with their fathers and grandfathers,
originally they are not.

264
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:26,000
Jîranên me ne û... cîranê me ne.
 
They are our neighbors and... our neighbors.

265
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:31,000
Aslan, ez dixwazim xalê Hesen çi tiştekî dest li xwendavanan
e gundî...
 
Exactly, I want uncle Hesen, whatever it is regarding the
students of the village...

266
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:37,000
Berê di her gundî de dibistan tune bû.. wan diçûn li kû derê
dixwendin... wexta?
 
Before, there wasn't a school in every village... where did
they go to study... at that time?

267
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:42,000
Em... qeçik bûn em da... em diçûn... Keferdelê dixwendin.
 
We... we were kids when we... we went... to study in
Keferdelê.

268
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,000
Belê... Xwendina we jî...
 
Yes... Your studying too...

269
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:47,000
Lê Keferdelê mekteb hebû, evwleli bidayê li Keferdelê.
 
But there was a school in Keferdelê, first of all in the
beginning it was in Keferdelê.

270
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,000
Dars pêk dihat li Keferdelê.
 
Classes took place in Keferdelê.

271
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:52,000
Em qeçik em şivan bûn em ne diçûn, Keferdelê mek...
 
We were kids, we were shepherds, we didn't go, Keferdelê
sch...

272
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:57,000
Dixwendin em di ber re demaşîn bi meşê diçûn, bi meşê
dihatin... ah.
 
They studied, we walked alongside, we went walking, we came
walking... ah.

273
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,000
Ma erebe tune bû wê jî?
 
Was there no car then either?

274
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Na, ew tune.
 
No, there wasn't.

275
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,000
Na mamo, tu rind nema girtiye, tu tiştekî nakî.
 
No uncle, you haven't remembered well, you are not doing
anything.

276
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:07,000
Û hayo, çendê we li xwendin, paşî yanî xwendin çû bajarê
Efrînê, çi qeder e...
 
And uncle, how much did you study, then I mean how much
studying was done in Afrin city...

277
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Heta... î şeşê. Şeşê şûnda em diçûn Efrînê.
 
Until... the sixth grade. After the sixth grade, we used to
go to Afrin.

278
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

279
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,000
Me li Efrînê xwend.
 
We studied in Afrin.

280
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:16,000
Na şeşê şûnda mekteb li Xazê vebû?
 
No, after the sixth grade, did the school open in Xazê?

281
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,000
Erê, erê.
 
Yes, yes.

282
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Paşê, dêmek em dixwazin hûn ji me ra behsa xwendinê li gundê
Xazê bikin.
 
Then, we want you to tell us about the education in Xazê
village.

283
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:27,000
Paşê mekteb hat gundê Xazê. Qeçkên gundê Xazê... çewa bû, çi
neba, ava kir, anîn gundê Xazê.
 
Then, the school came to Xazê village. The children of Xazê
village... whatever it was, they built it and brought it to
Xazê.

284
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Li Xazê orta... av.
 
In Xazê the middle... water.

285
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:34,000
Mekteb vebû. Şebab ha dixwend.
 
The school opened. The youth were studying.

286
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Ez dixwazim, tiştekî din jî li ser bixwînin, da ev gundî jî
dengê ken, yanî çiqa doktor ji vî gundî hene meselen.
 
I want you to talk about something else too, so the
villagers can also make their voices heard, I mean how many
doctors are from this village for example.

287
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Çi doktor te nas kirine? Di navê kî dîne jê me ra xeberek
din... muhamiyê vî gundî hene...
 
Which doctors did you know? Whose name is known, tell us
another word... are there lawyers from this village...

288
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,000
Eywa, li vî gundî me hene, erê.
 
Yes, there are in our village, yes.

289
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,000
Rengîn û Nazmî Elî...
 
Rengin and Nazmi Ali...

290
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:52,000
Xwedê jê razî be. Yanî em kenin, em li gundê Xazê da ne, va
çiqa piçûk e...
 
May God be pleased with him. I mean we look around, we are
in the village of Xazê, see how small it is...

291
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:57,000
Lê xwendewanên vî gundî hene... Û doktorên vî gundî hene...
 
But this village has students... And this village has
doctors...

292
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:03,000
Doktor jî hene, muhendîs jî pir in elhemdûlîllah. Muhendîsên
me di gundê me da cî hene. Mamosteyên erebî jî hene, û
mamosteyên fransî jî hene.
 
There are doctors, and there are many engineers, thank God.
We have engineers in our village. There are Arabic teachers,
and there are French teachers too.

293
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Yanî xwendewanên gundê me elhemdûlîllah gorî ta gundê me
piçûk e, bes xwendewanên me elhemdûlîllah yanî rind in.
 
I mean, the educated people of our village, thank God, even
though our village is small, but our students, thank God,
are good.

294
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:21,000
Cilkî bi serê xwe derketin, da xelkî merîk... tiştek
çêkirin... xwendewan bûn, derketin.
 
They managed on their own, so people... they built
something... they became educated, they graduated.

295
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Vêga noka ne ha cer... salek du sal in, disa, ceamet sê aqîz
e kena. Ha wisa doktor jî dixwînin, ên derkevin wa ne, hinek
jî doktor jî dixwînin va ye dê derkevin.
 
Now recently... it's been a year or two, again, the
community has three young ones. Like this, doctors are
studying, those who graduated are there, and some are
studying to be doctors and they will graduate.

296
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,000
Ev gulokên me ne... ev gulokên me em ji darê distînin e...
 
These are our rose petals... these are our rose petals we
take from the tree...

297
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:38,000
Paqij e, rind e. De kî lêçera gula çêkê, ez dixwazim piçek
ji me re bêjî, te çawa lêçera xwe ji gula çêdikî?
 
It's clean, it's good. So who makes the rose jam, I want you
to tell us a bit, how do you make your jam from roses?

298
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Yabo, em ev pelê gulê xwe tînin xwarê.
 
Oh man, we bring down our rose petals.

299
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,000
Me yê ev a nav vê qetran da...
 
We used to put this inside this pot...

300
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,000
Em didin hev, em dimistînin, şekirê xwe pê va dikir û, em
dimistînin û... dimistînin û... dimistînin û... ava qirêj jê
diçe...
 
Yes.

301
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Em didin hev, em dimistînin, şekirê xwe pê va dikir û, em
dimistînin û... dimistînin û... dimistînin û... ava qirêj jê
diçe...
 
We gather them, we mash them, we added our sugar to them,
and we mash them and... mash them and... mash them and...
the dirty water goes away from it...

302
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Em ev avê xwe bi parzûnê diparzinînin, zeriq xet, tiştekî
xweş. Em dîsa dimistînin, dimistînin û aha nav da mî...
 
Yes.

303
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:59,000
Em ev avê xwe bi parzûnê diparzinînin, zeriq xet, tiştekî
xweş. Em dîsa dimistînin, dimistînin û aha nav da mî...
 
We strain our water with a cheesecloth, it becomes bright,
something nice. We mash it again, mash it and it stays
inside like this...

304
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,000
We av diçirpande?
 
Did you sprinkle water?

305
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:12,000
Em ev cîntî xwet didin heba derê... em ev şerbeta xwe
dikelînin, vê xist e... me ev a şerbetê ew vî nav da
dikelîne. Em ava wê dikin nav. Ji xwe... ev dema bûrî, tişt
nema, em vê şûşê da dikin nav.
 
We put this nice stuff outside... we boil our syrup, put it
in... we boil this in the syrup. We put its water inside. By
itself... when this time passed, nothing remained, we put it
in the jars.

306
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,000
Du sê kelan xwar, me derxist e.
 
It boiled two or three times, we took it out.

307
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:18,000
Paşê ra me wekî toz lê kir, leymûn xozkê xwe jî dikirê...
 
Afterwards we put something like powder on it, we also put
our lemon salt in it...

308
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Û paşê me vî tiştkî dikira hênî... va me pêş... esê.
 
And then we made this thing like this... we put it... there.

309
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,000
Em vê jî şûşê dikin nan...
 
We put this in the jars too...

310
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:28,000
Sor dibû me derxist, xiste nîvîskê xwe. Wê nixte çi dîtir
nan, em nizanin.
 
It became red, we took it out, put it in its place. Now what
else there is, we don't know.

311
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:32,000
Xanimên gundî jî, lêçera gula weha çêdikin?
 
Do the women of the village also make rose jam like this?

312
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,000
Aha.
 
Yes.

313
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,000
Li gundî ew tiştan dikin?
 
Do they do these things in the village?

314
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:41,000
Li ba me jî wisa neçêdikin. Bes ez zanim... lêçera gula
hinek dikin, ne mîna min e, zû xera dibe tirş dibe. Gerek tu
wisa çêkî.
 
They don't make it like this here either. But I know... some
make rose jam, it's not like mine, it spoils quickly and
gets sour. You have to make it like this.

315
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,000
Berî wê ti tirş nabe?
 
Before that, it doesn't get sour?

316
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:53,000
Na... tirş nabe. Çawa me niha kir wê qasî, bi xist, tirş
nabe, ev xirab nabe tu carî ta şewqa we re bimîne, du sal e
bimîne li ba, tiştek nabe.
 
No... it doesn't get sour. The way we just did it that much,
if you put it, it doesn't get sour, this never goes bad even
if it stays with you until the light, even if it stays for
two years, nothing happens to it.

317
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:58,000
Te ji me re xeber da, te got ez li... çil pênc sal in, li
min, de li Helebê qey me da te bîra we de ye.
 
You talked to us, you said I have been... it's been 45 years
since I am here, so in Aleppo it's probably in your memory.

318
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:04,000
Gava tu derbasî vî gundî bûyî, te gişt gundê xelkê dît, her
tişt wek te giştî li te dît ne nuh bûn ji te re?
 
When you came to this village, you saw all the villagers,
did everything seem new to you like you saw everything?

319
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:10,000
Erê... Welle natka dulkholikî... xane... ha dibê em herin,
herr u ba dîtina cihe... reş ki... e.
 
Yes... By God... yes, they say let's go, let's go and see
the places...

320
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

321
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:24,000
Êxanê, tiştê pir hebûn, me ew pir dît... hey neqlê barî em
dikin... neql bi hêstira me bar dikirin... Me li hespan bar
dikir û dibirin... Me ev tiştan xist ser telî rê dixist...
 
Well, there were many things, we saw a lot of them... we
would load our transports... we used to load on mules... We
loaded on horses and took them... We put these things on the
wires and set them on the way...

322
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:31,000
Em diçûn û dor nediçû, em nedigihîşt... nuha jî barê me
dikin Toyota.
 
We used to go and it wouldn't end, we couldn't reach... now
they load our things into a Toyota.

323
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,000
Jin nema ne.
 
There are no women left.

324
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:35,000
Jin ketine paşerojê ya.
 
Women have fallen behind.

325
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,000
Çiqas dirêj e!
 
It is so long!

326
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:36,000
Amo berê nika çi qeder weha di...
 
Yes.

327
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:39,000
Amo berê nika çi qeder weha di...
 
Uncle, before, how much did they like this...

328
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:52,000
Erê her li oxura me pê da paşve... sê dest dor paşve, orğan
ji stînê. Di dî danin diya. Na me tanê we der, dî ova dek.
Nîka e, ev dirêj e tiştin ha da, di nav rê der e...
 
Yes, everything of ours was thrown back... three hands
around back, we took it from... We gave it to... Now, this
is long, there are things inside it, on the road...

329
00:23:52,000 --> 00:24:02,000
Bes teqeta me ne maye, xwedê dîsa da me nîvê mala xwe ava
bibe. Nuha ku diçîn cihek ter e, dernekeve. Da em... pere
hebin! Mar jî Bexdadê tê...
 
But our strength is gone, may God again make half of our
home prosper. Now if we go somewhere fresh, it doesn't
appear. If we have... money! Even a snake would come from
Baghdad...

330
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:11,000
Berê ku wekî wexta we dîtin li dor hev dizivirin, a malê da,
wa qerçebûn. Berî da def û zirne hebû, bi şev heya
pileyekî... bûk, cîhazê bûkê ne diçû.
 
Before, as you saw the times, they gathered around each
other, in the house, they were crowded. Before there was the
drum and zurna, at night until a certain degree... the
bride, the bride's dowry wouldn't go.

331
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:18,000
Xwe na... xela dikirin, na bî şew ne ma yabo. Dul hatin ha
diji qewqirandin e, dawa gund a jî..
 
They used to... gather, it wasn't left for the night man.
Drums came and deafened us, the village weddings too...

332
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:24,000
Bi hefteyek dikirin, li ser be der o. Cemiya gunde gîşt di
ne.
 
They used to do it for a week, outside. All the villagers
gathered.

333
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:30,000
(Music playing)
 
(Music playing)

334
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:50,000
Rabe hêşo min rabe, rabe min xamo min rabe... rabe hêşo min
rabe... rabe min xamo min rabe... Heger mirîk min hebî,
helal ser destê te be, heger mirîk min hebî, helal ser destê
te be.
 
Get up my green one get up, get up my raw one get up... get
up my green one get up... get up my raw one get up... If
death is for me, let it be allowed by your hands, if death
is for me, let it be allowed by your hands.

335
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:48,000
Welehî niha mekteb li gund heye? Qîçik tên...
 
By God, is there a school in the village now? The kids
come...

336
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:48,000
Û dermanxane û dixtor û şeydeleyî tiştên wa nîn in?
 
By God, currently, now there is a school in the village only
for the young kids... I mean there are only young
girls/boys. The school, doesn't operate for others
currently. Our kids go to Kafr Daleh, one by one they go to
Kafr Daleh, the children of the village.

337
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Û dermanxane û dixtor û şeydeleyî tiştên wa nîn in?
 
And there are no pharmacies, doctors, and pharmacies and
such things?

338
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Bîrên avê?
 
There's nothing.

339
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,000
Bîrên avê?
 
Water wells?

340
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,000
Bîr in avê hene.
 
There are water wells.

341
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:17,000
(Music playing)
 
(Music playing)

342
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:22,000
Mamê, bîra, pir marûf e yanî her kesê ku dûrî vî gundî jî,
tê li ser vê bîrê.
 
Uncle, the well, it's very famous, I mean anyone who is far
from this village too, comes to this well.

343
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:29,000
Jê keyf tê... ta çend wextan... ser bîrê û dar û dor,
muhebet û gundiyên he, gişt tên ser vê bîrê. Va bîra ji
kîjan wextî ve ye?
 
They enjoy it... until whatever time... around the well and
its surroundings, the conversation and the villagers, they
all come to this well. Since when has this well been here?

344
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:41,000
Ji dused sal e, de sêsed sal e, de çarsed sal e em
nizanin... da ye vir a. Tê bêjî bîr, bîra li vir in, bîra
emal e Îbrahîmê Hacî ye.
 
It's been two hundred years, maybe three hundred years,
maybe four hundred years, we don't know... it's here. If you
say well, the well here is, it's the well of the property of
Ibrahim Haji.

345
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:50,000
Û av balkî ba na milkê, di milkiyê me da ha ye e me ye..
yanî bîr bi xwê xastî xwe ke... rind e hewa wê...
 
And the water maybe in this property, in our property, it's
ours.. I mean the well has its own special thing... its air
is nice...

346
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:58,000
Û alem dihatin darên tûyê hebûn... darê qewaxê hebûn, gîha
hebûn, hinar hebûn... baxçe bûn.
 
And people would come, there were mulberry trees... there
were poplar trees, there was grass, there were
pomegranates... there were gardens.

347
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:11,000
Paşî ev aw qerebalix çû, bes bîrek maye... u çend darek man
e, xelk xwarinê dikirin, rûdiniştin derketin... avê xwe jî
got li vir buş ma xê te heta ku te vî wextê tî... ta şat
girin te bê piçkî bi...
 
Then all this crowd went away, only a well is left... and a
few trees are left, people used to make food, sit around and
go out... its water they said remained here a lot until this
time... it would keep flowing like a river until it became a
bit...

348
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:16,000
Û jimar jî xeber dan, gôtin avê vê bîrê qet hişk nabe.
 
And they told us, they said the water of this well never
dries up.

349
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:24,000
Qey hişk nabe, sal dwazde meh, wekî îsal çûyî piçûkek qet
tunebû...
 
Why wouldn't it dry up, twelve months a year, like this year
that passed there wasn't even a little bit...

350
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:32,000
Û ra ji binî... teqiya yanî zêde av ewku, wey bilind e ticî
dare...
 
And it exploded from the bottom... I mean a lot of water so
that, wow it's high, it's full of trees...

351
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:40,000
Û di derve jî rû de diherike diçe... tê dîtin.
 
And outside too it flows out on the surface... it can be
seen.

352
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,000
Çîroka va bîrê jî waha ye...
 
The story of this well is like this too...

353
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:49,000
Çîroka bîrê jî, bîr bi xwe esasi ye yanî. Ew mal e Îbrahîmê
Hecî ye. Mala me jî dibêjin mala Eşburcêne...
 
The story of the well too, the well itself is fundamental I
mean. It's the property of Ibrahim Haji. They call our
family the family of Ashburjene...

354
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:54,000
Ev ava tê qenî yê, ji erdê da herikiye jorda?
 
This water of the spring, does it flow from the earth
upwards?

355
00:28:54,000 --> 00:29:08,000
Ji jorda tê diherike ji jorda. Tê dît qenter e çêkirin e,
yanî berê, qenter e çêkirin e, û di girtin e... dorê çinar
ê, ku kanî be kî çêdibe da ye. Yanî ku dorê çinarek, yan
kaniyek be dît wisa xuya dibe na...
 
It comes from above, it flows from above. You saw they built
an arch, I mean in the past, they built an arch, and they
closed it... around the plane tree, if it's a spring, it's
built there. I mean if it's around a plane tree, or a
spring, it looks like that, doesn't it...

356
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:14,000
Em jî em sîpasiya we dikin... we demê xwe jimer vekirin
bîranîn wan da ro hîştin.
 
We also thank you... you gave your time to us and left these
memories for the day.

357
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:18,000
Ehlen we sehlen ro bareve, ro sihetxweş be bi hatina we re
serçava te te me barem xelo.
 
Welcome, may your day be fruitful, may you have good health,
with your arrival you are welcome upon my eyes, uncle.

358
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:21,000
Ser gundê Xazê me merivên qenc dîtin em dizanin bi, em kî dî
naskirin.
 
In the village of Xazê we saw good people, we know, we got
to know them.

359
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:31,000
Em dixwazin tenê sûretek xweş dîmenek xweş ji ser bajarê xwe
bixwînin, da xelk bibînin vên ciwanên nuh digirin zanebin va
gundê me navî gundê me anîn jor v'elhemdûlîllah bi serbilind
in gişt gundê xortên rûniştin in.
 
We want to show only a nice picture, a nice view from our
city, so people can see the new youth growing up, so they
know this is our village, they brought the name of our
village up, and thank God we are proud of all the youth
sitting in the village.

360
